    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut the <strong>lettuce</strong> into quarters lengthways – these are your <strong>lettuce wedges</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>tomato ketchup</strong> and<strong> soy sauce </strong>in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [200ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>with most of your <strong>cider vinegar</strong> (save the rest for later!) – this is your <strong>BBQ sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1684236508674-x200.jpg",
