            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chips are almost cooked, cut a slit into the top of your<strong> hot dog bun[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>cut</strong> <strong>hot dog bun[s]</strong> to a separate baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 2-3 min or until warmed through</p><p>Add the <strong>lettuce wedges</strong> to a bowl with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong>, the <strong>remaining cider vinegar</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mix it all together – these are your <strong>dressed wedges</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1684236530443-x200.jpg",
